\begin{align*}
2x-5 &= \frac{x+5}{2}\\
4x-10 &= x+5\\
3x &= 15\\
x &= \boxed{5}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the value of $x$ such that $f(x) = f^{-1}(x)$ is $\boxed{5}$.

